  5	    refactor(cms)(draft-editor): editDocument + applyImageUpload + publish
  6	    
  7	    Add the three write operations to DraftEditor, each addressed by ContentScope
  8	    and routed through scopeKeys:
  9	    - editDocument: encode current → deepMerge(override) → decode (400 IssueError
 10	      on reject) → re-encode → store at the scope's draft key; returns EncodedDoc.
 11	    - applyImageUpload: rewrite a targeted …key field on the draft (raw-bytes
 12	      upload + content-type gate stay in the route).
 13	    - publish: promote the scope's current edit source to the published key, drop
 14	      the draft best-effort, bust the public read cache; 502 IssueError on a
 15	      storage failure.
 16	    
 17	    A decoded document always re-encodes, so encode-after-decode dies rather than
 18	    masquerading as an IssueError. defaultLayer pre-provides ONE shared Storage so
 19	    publish's bust hits the cache the public read serves from.
 20	    
 21	    Route still calls the old inline pipeline; behavior identical (migrated in
 22	    1.3). Tests prove merge preserves unedited deep fields, the present-but-empty
 23	    required field rejects, image-key rewrite persists, and publish goes live on
 24	    the next read.
